# The AI coach is provider-switchable. Set ONE of the keys below.
# If both are set, Gemini (free) is used unless you override with
# ARTICULATE_PROVIDER below.

# --- Option A: Google Gemini (free tier, recommended) ---
# Get a free key at https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey  (no credit card)
GEMINI_API_KEY=
# Optional: override the Gemini model (defaults to gemini-2.5-flash-lite)
# GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash-lite

# --- Option B: Anthropic Claude (paid) ---
# Get a key at https://console.anthropic.com/
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# Optional: override the Claude model (defaults to claude-opus-4-8)
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-opus-4-8

# --- Optional: force a provider regardless of which keys are present ---
# ARTICULATE_PROVIDER=gemini   # or: claude

# --- Per-user AI allowance (signed-in users only) ---
# Each signed-in user gets an annual AI-feedback spend cap so one account can
# never run up the AI bill. The cap is sized by their plan (1/3 of the annual
# price per purchased level; Free = $1 trial — see lib/tiers.ts) and renews on a
# rolling window. Only the window length is env-configurable (default 365 days):
# USER_ALLOWANCE_DAYS=365

# --- Comp / full-access accounts (OPTIONAL) ---
# Comma-separated emails (or usernames) that get full Max-tier access with NO
# subscription and an uncapped AI allowance. Kept in env (not code) so the
# addresses stay private. Create the accounts normally via sign-up, then list
# their emails here.
# COMP_USER_EMAILS=you+admin1@gmail.com,you+admin2@gmail.com,you+admin3@gmail.com

# --- Authentication (Clerk) — OPTIONAL ---
# Leave these blank to run auth-disabled: every page works, drills are
# practiceable, and progress is saved locally (no accounts, no cross-device
# sync). Set both keys to enable sign up / login and per-account progress.
# Create a free app at https://dashboard.clerk.com and copy both keys.
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
CLERK_SECRET_KEY=
# Optional: Clerk webhook (Dashboard -> Webhooks) pointing at .../api/clerk/webhook
# for the `user.deleted` event — cancels the user's Stripe subscriptions when
# their account is deleted. Paste the endpoint's signing secret here.
CLERK_WEBHOOK_SIGNING_SECRET=

# --- Subscriptions (Stripe) — OPTIONAL ---
# Leave blank to run without paid plans (pricing page shows tiers, but checkout
# returns 503 and everyone stays on Free). To enable annual subscriptions:
#   1. Create ONE Stripe product with four ANNUAL recurring prices:
#        $4.99 (Starter), $9.99 (Plus), $19.99 (Pro), $49.99 (Max).
#   2. Paste the secret key and the four price IDs below.
#   3. Add a webhook to .../api/billing/webhook for events:
#        checkout.session.completed, customer.subscription.created,
#        customer.subscription.updated, customer.subscription.deleted
#      and paste its signing secret as STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET.
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
STRIPE_PRICE_STARTER=
STRIPE_PRICE_PLUS=
STRIPE_PRICE_PRO=
STRIPE_PRICE_MAX=

# --- Site URL (OPTIONAL) ---
# Canonical origin used for SEO metadata, Open Graph, sitemap, and robots URLs.
# Defaults to https://iarticulate.ca (see lib/site.ts); override for a fork or
# staging deployment.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://iarticulate.ca
